David de Coninck or David de Koninck, also known as Rammelaer (ca. 1644, Antwerp â€“ after 1701, probably Brussels) was a Flemish painter who specialised in still lifes and landscapes with animals and hunting scenes. Recognised as a leading animal painter, de Coninck was able to develop an international career which caused him to work for extended periods in Paris, Rome and Vienna.


